    <!-- Topic modelling -->
    <div class="card visualization-card mb-5">
        <div class="card-body">
            <h4 class="card-title">4. Topic modelling</h4>
            <p class="card-text">Non-negative Matrix Factorization (NMF) was used to identify 5 distinct topics in the review corpus, providing insights into the main themes and concerns expressed by customers.</p>
            <div class="text-center">
                <img src="static/images/nlp/topic_distribution.png" alt="Topic Distribution" class="img-fluid viz-img">
                <figcaption class="text-muted mt-2">Distribution of identified topics across the review dataset, showing the prevalence of each theme.</figcaption>
            </div>
            <div class="mt-4">
                <h5>Identified Topics and Key Terms</h5>
                <table class="table table-bordered">
                    <thead class="table-light">
                        <tr>
                            <th>Topic</th>
                            <th>Top Words</th>
                            <th>Interpretation</th>
                        </tr>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody>
                        <tr>
                            <td>Topic 1</td>
                            <td>battery, life, charge, last, long, day, hour</td>
                            <td>Battery Life and Charging</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td>Topic 2</td>
                            <td>screen, display, quality, resolution, bright, color, touch</td>
                            <td>Display Quality</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td>Topic 3</td>
                            <td>price, value, money, worth, cost, expensive, cheap</td>
                            <td>Price and Value</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td>Topic 4</td>
                            <td>camera, picture, photo, quality, video, image, take</td>
                            <td>Camera Quality</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td>Topic 5</td>
                            <td>performance, fast, speed, slow, lag, processor, run</td>
                            <td>Performance and Speed</td>
                        </tr>
                    </tbody>
                </table>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    
    <!-- Aspect-Based Sentiment Analysis -->
    <div class="card visualization-card">
        <div class="card-body">
            <h4 class="card-title">5. Aspect-Based Sentiment Analysis</h4>
            <p class="card-text">By analyzing sentiment specifically for different product aspects (features), we gained detailed insights into which features customers liked or disliked across products.</p>
            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-md-6">
                    <div class="text-center">
                        <img src="static/images/nlp/aspect_mentions.png" alt="Aspect Mentions" class="img-fluid viz-img">
                        <figcaption class="text-muted mt-2">Frequency of aspect mentions across all reviews, showing which features customers discuss most often.</figcaption>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="col-md-6">
                    <div class="text-center">
                        <img src="static/images/nlp/aspect_sentiment.png" alt="Aspect Sentiment" class="img-fluid viz-img">
                        <figcaption class="text-muted mt-2">Average sentiment score for each aspect, highlighting the features that receive most positive and negative feedback.</figcaption>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="mt-4">
                <div class="text-center">
                    <img src="static/images/nlp/aspect_sentiment_heatmap.png" alt="Aspect Sentiment Heatmap" class="img-fluid viz-img">
                    <figcaption class="text-muted mt-2">Heatmap showing sentiment scores for each aspect across different products, providing a comprehensive view of strengths and weaknesses.</figcaption>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="mt-4">
                <h5>Key Aspect-Based Insights</h5>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Battery:</strong> Most frequently mentioned aspect (236 mentions), with mixed sentiment (-0.12 for Budget Phone, +0.65 for Tablet Mini)</li>
                    <li><strong>Display:</strong> Second most mentioned aspect (214 mentions), generally positive sentiment (+0.47 average)</li>
                    <li><strong>Performance:</strong> Wide variation in sentiment across products (+0.72 for Laptop Pro, -0.23 for Budget Phone)</li>
                    <li><strong>Price:</strong> Most negative aspect for premium products (-0.15 for Smartphone X), positive for Budget Phone (+0.58)</li>
                    <li><strong>Camera:</strong> Highly polarized aspect (strongest positive for Smartphone X at +0.76, strongest negative for Budget Phone at -0.36)</li>
                    <li><strong>Sound:</strong> Highest overall sentiment (+0.78) for Headphones Ultra</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<!-- Conclusions Section -->
<section class="container mb-5">
    <h2 class="section-title">Conclusions & Recommendations</h2>
    <div class="card border-0 shadow">
        <div class="card-body">
            <h4 class="mb-3">Key Product Insights</h4>
            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-md-6">
                    <h5>Product Strengths</h5>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Headphones Ultra:</strong> Industry-leading sound quality and comfort, excellent battery life (90% positive sentiment)</li>
                        <li><strong>Smartphone X:</strong> Superior camera quality, premium display, decent battery life (80% positive sentiment)</li>
                        <li><strong>Laptop Pro:</strong> Strong performance, high-quality display, good build quality (70% positive sentiment)</li>
                        <li><strong>Tablet Mini:</strong> Excellent battery life, portable design, good display (60% positive sentiment)</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div class="col-md-6">
                    <h5>Areas for Improvement</h5>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Budget Phone:</strong> Poor camera quality, performance issues, battery longevity (30% positive sentiment)</li>
                        <li><strong>Smart Watch:</strong> Battery drain issues, limited functionality (50% positive sentiment)</li>
                        <li><strong>Digital Camera:</strong> Mixed reviews on price-to-performance ratio (60% positive sentiment)</li>
                        <li><strong>Smartphone X:</strong> Price concerns, software bugs mentioned in some reviews</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
            
</section>


